  "birth_place": "Königsberg",
  "description": "German philosopher (1730-1788)",
  "bio": "約翰·格奧爾格·哈曼（Johann Georg Hamann，德語：[ˈhaːman]；1730年8月27日—1788年6月21日）是來自柯尼斯堡的德國路德派哲學家，被稱為「北方巫師」，是後康德哲學的領袖人物之一。他的學生赫爾德將他的作品用作狂飆突進運動的主要支持者，並與反啟蒙運動和浪漫主義有關。  \n他向同樣來自柯尼斯堡的康德介紹了休謨（將他從「教條式的沉睡」中喚醒）和盧梭的作品。哈曼受到休謨的影響，但他用他的觀點來支援而不是反對基督教。\n歌德和克爾凱郭爾都認為他是他那個時代最優秀的人。他也對黑格爾和弗里德里希·海因裡希·雅各比有重要影響。 早在語言學轉向之前，哈曼就認為，認識論應該被語言哲學取代。",
  "bio_source": "zhwiki",
  "description_en": "German philosopher (1730-1788)",
  "bio_en": "Johann Georg Hamann (; German: [ˈhaːman]; 27 August 1730 – 21 June 1788) was a German Lutheran philosopher from Königsberg. Known by the pen name \"the Magus (Wizard) of the North\", he was one of the leading figures of post-Kantian philosophy. His work was used by his student Johann Gottfried Herder as the main support of the Sturm und Drang movement, and is associated with the Counter-Enlightenment and Romanticism.\nHe introduced Kant, also from Königsberg, to the works of both Hume – which Kant credited with waking him from his \"dogmatic slumber\" – and Rousseau.",
  "bio_en_source": "enwiki"
}